<subSubSection lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="54.[136,1452,1903,2074]" lastBlockId="55.[136,1452,158,1301]" lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,291,2011,2037]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Habitat:</emphasis>
—In Brazilian territory, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; J. R. Laundon" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch ex Diels" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[571,711,2012,2037]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis box="[571,711,2012,2037]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">D. roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only found on the highlands of the tepuis and other northern Amazonic mountains, growing in sandy or peaty soils and in cracks of sandstone or quartzite. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1189,1307,2048,2074]" name="Venezuela" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; J. R. Laundon" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch ex Diels" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1316,1451,2048,2073]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis box="[1316,1451,2048,2073]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">D. roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs in upland plains, growing in sandy to peaty soils in wet areas of the Gran Sabana. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1239,1310,158,184]" name="Brazil" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, collected at 
<quantity box="[136,277,194,221]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.73" metricValueMin="0.47" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="2730.0" valueMin="470.0">470–2730 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[136,1452,158,1301]" box="[189,669,230,256]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,230,256]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Found in flower year-round.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="55.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,436,266,292]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—Least Concern (LC). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; J. R. Laundon" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch ex Diels" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[701,903,267,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis box="[701,903,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Drosera roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in a relatively remote area in three South American countries (
<collectingCountry box="[451,525,302,328]" name="Brazil" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: AOO= 
<quantity box="[614,687,302,328]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="km" value="64.0">64 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[687,695,302,316]" fontSize="6" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">2</superScript>
, EOO= 
<quantity box="[786,923,302,329]" metricMagnitude="8" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.561" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="km" value="156100.0">156,100 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[922,930,302,316]" fontSize="6" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">2</superScript>
; global: AOO= 
<quantity box="[1110,1199,302,328]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="km" value="420.0">420 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1199,1207,302,316]" fontSize="6" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">2</superScript>
, EOO= 
<quantity box="[1296,1434,302,329]" metricMagnitude="8" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5146" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="km" value="351460.0">351,460 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1434,1442,302,316]" fontSize="6" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">2</superScript>
) where no severe threat is reported. In 
<collectingCountry box="[557,628,338,364]" name="Brazil" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it has been recorded from the Pico da Neblina (AM) and Monte 
<collectingRegion box="[1355,1451,338,364]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Roraima</collectingRegion>
(RR) National Parks as well as Serra do Aracá State Park (AM).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,410,436]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; J. R. Laundon" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch ex Diels" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[294,495,411,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis box="[294,495,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Drosera roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[764,911,411,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis box="[764,911,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">D. communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which also occurs on the uplands of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1364,1451,410,436]" name="Guyana" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Guyana</collectingCountry>
Shield, although the two are apparently never syntopic. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[937,1087,447,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis box="[937,1087,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">D. communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1288,446,472]" name="Guyana" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Guyana</collectingCountry>
Shield can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; J. R. Laundon" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch ex Diels" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[438,579,483,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis box="[438,579,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">D. roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by more slender habit and usually the formation of shorter columns, with marcescent leaves conspicuously reflexed, the laxer rosettes with glabrescent leaves, and most reliably by the narrowly obovate lamina and fusiform seed shape.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Although all specimens examined from 
<collectingCountry box="[633,701,590,616]" name="Brazil" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
present glandular trichomes on the inflorescences, a few specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; J. R. Laundon" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch ex Diels" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[168,306,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis box="[168,306,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">D. roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with completely glabrous scapes, pedicels and sepals were studied from 
<collectingCountry box="[1140,1259,626,652]" name="Venezuela" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. These and other unusual specimens of the variable 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; J. R. Laundon" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch ex Diels" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[534,673,663,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roraimae">
<emphasis box="[534,673,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">D. roraimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can nonetheless be safely distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maguire &amp; Wurdack" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Steyermark" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1205,1370,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="esmeraldae">
<emphasis box="[1205,1370,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">D. esmeraldae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more robust habit, usually stem forming, the semi-erect leaves and the ellipsoid to rectangular seed with reticulate testa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Diels" authorityYear="1914" box="[189,539,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="montana" variety="robusta">
<emphasis box="[189,391,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Drosera montana</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[454,539,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the specimen 
<emphasis box="[1000,1107,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ule 8610</emphasis>
, of which two duplicates are known, at B and K. Since 
<bibRefCitation author="Diels, L." box="[433,574,806,832]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="136" refId="ref54233" refString="Diels, L. (1914) Droseraceae. In: Pilger, R. (ed.) Plantae Uleanae novae vel minus cognitae 1. Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum, Berlin-Dahlem. pp. 136." type="book chapter" year="1914">Diels (1914)</bibRefCitation>
does not indicate the herbarium where the original material was studied, both specimens are considered 
<typeStatus box="[428,529,843,869]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">syntypes</typeStatus>
, making it necessary to select a 
<typeStatus box="[885,991,842,868]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Correa A. &amp; Silva, T. R. S." box="[1001,1251,842,869]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref53788" refString="Correa A., M. D. &amp; Silva, T. R. S. (2005) Drosera (Droseraceae). Flora Neotropica Monograph 96. The New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 65 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Correa &amp; 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann, 2022" authorityName="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann" authorityYear="2022" box="[1112,1170,842,868]" class="Aves" family="Leiothrichidae" genus="Silva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="55" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Silva</taxonomicName>
(2005)
</bibRefCitation>
cite the specimen at K as the “ 
<typeStatus box="[270,375,878,904]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">holotype</typeStatus>
”, however, without including the words “here designated” it cannot be interpreted as inadvertent lectotypification since the year 2001 (ICN Art. 7.11, 
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[752,979,914,940]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref59430" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (eds.) 2018: International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[850,909,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), hence that name has not been properly lectotypified. Thus, we here select the specimen held at B as the 
<typeStatus box="[845,951,950,976]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">lectotype</typeStatus>
, since it is the specimen personally annotated by Diels at the herbarium where he originally worked at the time he published that name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
